        <h1>Welcome to the Mining App</h1>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="card mb-4">
                    <div class="card-header">A Message from the CEO</div>
                    <div class="card-body text-center">
                        <img src="me.jpeg" alt="Muhammad Zubair" class="rounded-circle" style="width: 120px; height: 120px; margin-bottom: 15px;"> <!-- Replace with your image path -->
                        <h5 class="card-title">Welcome to the Mining App!</h5>
                        <p>Hi there! I'm Muhammad Zubair, the CEO and Owner of this platform. I am passionate about empowering individuals in the world of cryptocurrency. Our mission is to provide you with the best tools and resources to succeed in your mining journey.</p>
                        <p>Thank you for joining us, and let's explore the exciting world of cryptocurrency mining together!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        

        <div class="articles">
            <h2>Articles and Information</h2>
            <p>Here you can find various articles about mining and cryptocurrency.</p>
            <p>Stay updated with the latest trends and news in the mining industry.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Cryptocurrency Information Sections -->
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <div class="card mb-3">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <img src="https://cryptologos.cc/logos/bitcoin-btc-logo.png" alt="Bitcoin" class="card-icon"> Bitcoin
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">The First Decentralized Cryptocurrency</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Bitcoin is a peer-to-peer currency that allows online payments to be sent directly from one party to another without going through a financial institution.</p>
                        <h6>History:</h6>
                        <p>Launched in 2009 by an anonymous person or group using the name Satoshi Nakamoto, Bitcoin was the first cryptocurrency and remains the most valuable and popular.</p>
                        <h6>Security:</h6>
                        <p>Bitcoin transactions are secured by cryptography and are recorded on a public ledger known as the blockchain.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-3">
                <div class="card mb-3">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <img src="https://cryptologos.cc/logos/ethereum-eth-logo.png" alt="Ethereum" class="card-icon"> Ethereum
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Decentralized Platform That Runs Smart Contracts</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Ethereum is a decentralized platform that enables smart contracts and decentralized applications to be built and run without any downtime, fraud, control, or interference from a third party.</p>
                        <h6>History:</h6>
                        <p>Launched in 2015 by Vitalik Buterin and a group of co-founders, Ethereum has grown to be the second-largest cryptocurrency by market cap.</p>
                        <h6>Security:</h6>
                        <p>Ethereum transactions are also secured by cryptographic algorithms and utilize a blockchain that facilitates smart contracts.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-3">
                <div class="card mb-3">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <img src="https://cryptologos.cc/logos/cardano-ada-logo.png" alt="Cardano" class="card-icon"> Cardano
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">A Blockchain Platform for Smart Contracts</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Cardano is a blockchain platform that is designed to be more secure and scalable than other blockchain systems.</p>
                        <h6>History:</h6>
                        <p>Launched in 2017 by Charles Hoskinson, one of the co-founders of Ethereum, Cardano aims to create a balanced and sustainable ecosystem for cryptocurrencies.</p>
                        <h6>Security:</h6>
                        <p>Cardano uses a proof-of-stake consensus mechanism called Ouroboros, which aims to provide better security and energy efficiency.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-3">
                <div class="card mb-3">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <img src="https://cryptologos.cc/logos/ripple-xrp-logo.png" alt="Ripple" class="card-icon"> Ripple
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Digital Payment Protocol and Cryptocurrency</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">Ripple enables secure, instant, and low-cost international payments of any size without chargebacks.</p>
                        <h6>History:</h6>
                        <p>Ripple was launched in 2012 as a payment protocol and has since grown to support numerous financial institutions globally.</p>
                        <h6>Security:</h6>
                        <p>Ripple uses a consensus ledger that validates transactions across its network, ensuring the integrity and security of the system.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Blockchain Information Section -->
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="card mb-3">
                    <div class="card-header" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Understanding Blockchain Technology</div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header">What Is Blockchain?</div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Blockchain is a decentralized ledger of all transactions across a network. This technology ensures transparency and security, making it a vital component of cryptocurrencies.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header">How It Works</div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Transactions are grouped into blocks and added to a chain in a linear, chronological order. Each block contains a cryptographic hash of the previous block, ensuring that once a block is added, it cannot be altered without altering all subsequent blocks.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header">Security</div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>The decentralized nature of blockchain means that it is less vulnerable to attacks. Data is stored across multiple nodes, and consensus mechanisms prevent unauthorized changes to the ledger.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
